{"title":"KMC REACT Cassettes join their 10/11-Speed Chains","link":"https://bikerumor.com/kmc-react-cassettes/","date":1707375900000,"content":"<p><img width=\"2157\" height=\"1297\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/kmc-react-11-50-11speed-cassette.jpg\" alt=\"KMC REACT 11-speed chain\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/kmc-react-11-50-11speed-cassette.jpg 2157w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/kmc-react-11-50-11speed-cassette-297x179.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/kmc-react-11-50-11speed-cassette-800x481.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/kmc-react-11-50-11speed-cassette-120x72.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/kmc-react-11-50-11speed-cassette-768x462.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/kmc-react-11-50-11speed-cassette-1536x924.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/kmc-react-11-50-11speed-cassette-2048x1231.jpg 2048w\" /></p>\n<p>Long-time bicycle chain brand KMC has just introduced their new React cassettes in 10-speed and 11-speed versions. They’re designed for wide-range 1x and 2x applications, with tooth counts good for road, gravel, and mountain bikes.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>At just $65, they’re affordable replacement, option for your trainer, or way to try a different tooth count on the cheap. Perfect for upgrading your kids’ bikes, too. And from the looks of it, you won’t be giving up shift quality to save some coin.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"1300\" height=\"827\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/KMC-react-cassette-tooth-ramp-highlights.jpg\" alt=\"KMC react cassette shift ramp highlights\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/KMC-react-cassette-tooth-ramp-highlights.jpg 1300w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/KMC-react-cassette-tooth-ramp-highlights-297x189.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/KMC-react-cassette-tooth-ramp-highlights-800x509.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/KMC-react-cassette-tooth-ramp-highlights-120x76.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/KMC-react-cassette-tooth-ramp-highlights-768x489.jpg 768w\" />\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t        <div>\n                \n                    \n                \n                <div>\n<figure><img alt=\"KMC react cassette shift ramp highlights\" /></figure>\n</div>\n                <div>\n<figure><img alt=\"KMC react cassette shift ramp highlights\" /></figure>\n</div>\n                <div></div>\n        </div></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The cogs have dual shifting ramps called Flow Control, smoothing upshift and downshifts. These ramped tooth profiles &amp; thicknesses use varied shapes to guide the chain from cog to cog.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"1300\" height=\"633\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/kmc-react-gear-ratio-tooth-counts-chart.jpg\" alt=\"KMC react cassette tooth counts\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/kmc-react-gear-ratio-tooth-counts-chart.jpg 1300w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/kmc-react-gear-ratio-tooth-counts-chart-297x145.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/kmc-react-gear-ratio-tooth-counts-chart-800x390.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/kmc-react-gear-ratio-tooth-counts-chart-120x58.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/kmc-react-gear-ratio-tooth-counts-chart-768x374.jpg 768w\" />\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t        <div>\n                \n                    \n                \n                <div>\n<figure><img alt=\"KMC react cassette tooth counts\" /></figure>\n</div>\n                <div>\n<figure><img alt=\"KMC react cassette tooth counts\" /></figure>\n</div>\n                <div></div>\n        </div></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Both KMC REACT versions have two gear range options:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>10-speed: 11-36T, 11-42T</li>\n\n\n\n<li>11-speed: 11-42T, 11-50T</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"1952\" height=\"1064\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/kmc-react-36-42-tooth-cassettes.jpg\" alt=\"KMC REACT 10-speed chains\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/kmc-react-36-42-tooth-cassettes.jpg 1952w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/kmc-react-36-42-tooth-cassettes-297x162.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/kmc-react-36-42-tooth-cassettes-800x436.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/kmc-react-36-42-tooth-cassettes-120x65.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/kmc-react-36-42-tooth-cassettes-768x419.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/kmc-react-36-42-tooth-cassettes-1536x837.jpg 1536w\" />\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t        <div>\n                \n                    \n                \n                <div>\n<figure><img alt=\"KMC REACT 10-speed chains\" /></figure>\n</div>\n                <div>\n<figure><img alt=\"KMC REACT 10-speed chains\" /></figure>\n</div>\n                <div></div>\n        </div></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>They’re optimized for KMC chains, but are compatible with other 10- and 11-speed chains. They fit Shimano HG freehub bodies. Fitting it to a bike built around a smaller cassette? They recommend adding the <a href=\"https://www.wolftoothcomponents.com/search?q=goatlink\">Wolf Tooth Components Goatlink</a> to increase your derailleur’s capacity for larger cogs.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.kmcchain.us\" target=\"_blank\">KMCchain.us</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/kmc-react-cassettes/\">KMC REACT Cassettes join their 10/11-Speed Chains</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Tyler Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"c14028bc2f1e8558870b024c11be55d6fe399da56ca5935cf81cc1101e5a17e3","category":"Cycling"}